Welcome to Ingestors’s documentation!

Ingestors extract useful information in a structured standard format.

   Free software: MIT license
   Documentation: https://ingestors.readthedocs.io.

  TODO

Installation

To install Ingestors, use pip or add it to your project dependencies.



  $ pip install ingestors



If you don’t have pip installed, this Python installation guide can guide you through the process.

Documentation

The documentation for Ingestors is available at ingestors.readthedocs.io.


Feel free to edit the source files in the docs folder and send pull requests for improvements.


To build the documentation, please install the dependencies first and run make docs :



  $ pip install -r requirements_dev.txt
  $ make docs



Now you can browse the documentation locally at http://localhost:8000/docs/_build/html/ :



  $ make docs-web
